LAGOS – The Minister of State for Health, Senator Olorun­nibe Mamora, has urged healthcare providers in Nigeria to parley with the federal and state govern­ments to bring healthcare facilities to the doorsteps of Nigerians. Speaking at the Annu­al Scientific Conference and 16th National Annual General Meeting (AGM) of the Healthcare Provid­ers Association of Nigeria (HCPAN), in Ikeja, Lagos, Mamora commended the association for contribut­ing immensely to the devel­opment of the healthcare system in Nigerian. Mamora, who was repre­sented at the conference by Prof. Chris Bode, the Chief Medical Director (CMD) of the Lagos University Teaching Hospital (LUTH), stressed the need for the private sector to partner effectively with both feder­al and state governments to upgrade the health facil­ities in the country. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He noted that the fight against COVID-19 was still on, even as he appealed to Nigerians to follow the protocol as laid down by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC). SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION